ZH: 我们之间建立起了信任关系。
EN: We have established a relationship of trust between us.

ZH: 信任是一个良好的团队合作的基础。
EN: Trust is the foundation of good teamwork.

ZH: 只有信任，我们才能更好地合作。
EN: Only with trust can we collaborate better.

ZH: 他赢得了我的信任，我相信他会做出正确的决定。
EN: He has earned my trust, and I believe he will make the right decision.

ZH: 不要轻易失去他人的信任，这是很难重新得到的。
EN: Do not easily lose the trust of others, as it is difficult to regain.

ZH: 信任需要时间来建立和加强。
EN: Trust takes time to build and strengthen.

ZH: 他一再犯错，让人难以再次信任他。
EN: He keeps making mistakes, making it hard to trust him again.

ZH: 我感到非常荣幸，他选择了我来做他的信任人。
EN: I feel incredibly honored that he chose me to be his confidant.

ZH: 信任是两人之间最重要的纽带之一。
EN: Trust is one of the most important bonds between two individuals.

ZH: 没有信任，没有任何关系能够持久。
EN: Without trust, no relationship can last.

ZH: 我们必须彼此信任，才能共同实现目标。
EN: We must trust each other in order to achieve our goals together.

ZH: 坦诚与信任是一个健康的友谊必备的特质。
EN: Honesty and trust are essential qualities for a healthy friendship.

ZH: 某些行为会破坏别人对我们的信任。
EN: Certain actions can damage other people's trust in us.

ZH: 她的信任摧毁了他对她的感情。
EN: Her betrayal destroyed his trust in her.

ZH: 我已经学会了重新信任他，尽管他过去犯过错误。
EN: I have learned to trust him again, despite his past mistakes.

ZH: 他对我毫不怀疑，总是给我充分的信任。
EN: He never doubts me and always gives me his full trust.

ZH: 信任是建立在互相理解和支持的基础上的。
EN: Trust is built on a foundation of mutual understanding and support.

ZH: 我在他的帮助下克服了困难，因此对他充满了信任。
EN: I overcame difficulties with his help, so I have complete trust in him.

ZH: 拥有信任感的人更容易建立良好的人际关系。
EN: People who have a sense of trust are more likely to build good interpersonal relationships.

ZH: 信任是一个长期的投资，但它是值得的。
EN: Trust is a long-term investment, but it is worth it.
